          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flashcard" onclick="this.classList.toggle('flipped')">
        <div class="flashcard-inner">
          <div class="flashcard-front">
            <div class="fc-q">Question</div>
            <div class="fc-text">What is a "Train Wreck" code smell?</div>
            <div class="fc-hint">tap to flip →</div>
          </div>
          <div class="flashcard-back">
            <div class="fc-a">Answer</div>
            <div class="fc-text">Chained method calls: <code>a.getB().getC().getD()</code> — violates the Law of Demeter by calling methods on returned strangers.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flashcard" onclick="this.classList.toggle('flipped')">
        <div class="flashcard-inner">
          <div class="flashcard-front">
