    <!-- All 13 naming rules summary -->
    <div class="wide-card" style="margin-top:2rem">
      <div class="wc-title">📋 All 13 Naming Rules at a Glance</div>
      <table class="comp-table">
        <tr>
          <th>#</th>
          <th>Rule</th>
          <th>Key Point</th>
          <th>Memory Cue</th>
        </tr>
        <tr><td>1</td><td><strong>Intention-Revealing</strong></td><td>Name answers: why, what, how</td><td>No name → needs comment → bad name</td></tr>
        <tr><td>2</td><td><strong>Avoid Disinformation</strong></td><td>No false clues, no l/O confusion</td><td>l = 1, O = 0 → dirty hack to change font</td></tr>
        <tr><td>3</td><td><strong>Meaningful Distinctions</strong></td><td>Different names → different meanings</td><td>a1/a2 = noninformative, not just different</td></tr>
        <tr><td>4</td><td><strong>Eliminate Noise</strong></td><td>No variable/table/data/info suffixes</td><td>NameString vs Name — same thing!</td></tr>
        <tr><td>5</td><td><strong>Searchable Names</strong></td><td>Constants must be named, not magic</td><td>Can you Ctrl+F it? If not, rename</td></tr>
        <tr><td>6</td><td><strong>Class Names → Noun</strong></td><td>WHO? → Noun/Noun phrase</td><td>Never a verb. Never Manager/Data/Info</td></tr>
        <tr><td>7</td><td><strong>Method Names → Verb</strong></td><td>WHAT? → Verb/Verb phrase</td><td>Static factory > overloaded constructors</td></tr>
        <tr><td>8</td><td><strong>Avoid Encodings</strong></td><td>No Hungarian Notation (iAge, strName)</td><td>Microsoft said NO since 2008</td></tr>
        <tr><td>9</td><td><strong>Pronounceable Names</strong></td><td>Can you say it out loud?</td><td>Programming = social activity</td></tr>
        <tr><td>10</td><td><strong>Avoid Mental Mapping</strong></td><td>Don't make readers translate r,t,p</td><td>i,j,k for loops = OK (universal)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>11</td><td><strong>Don't Be Cute</strong></td><td>whack() → kill(). Say what you mean.</td><td>Jokes expire. Names don't.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>12</td><td><strong>One Word Per Concept</strong></td><td>get/fetch/retrieve = pick ONE</td><td>Consistent lexicon = gift to coworkers</td></tr>
        <tr><td>13</td><td><strong>Add Context</strong></td><td>addrState > state (prefix or class)</td><td>state alone = ambiguous</td></tr>
      </table>
